<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-239-348  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 239 348.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  May 3 1989 n1168* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Motorola looks to sew up premium cellular market with 9800Xmini-phone. (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Motorola Inc. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    MOT.andO;Product:   Motorola 9800X Personal Celluphone (Telephone) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Cellular RadioTelephonesProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>MOTOROLA LOOKS TO SEW UP PREMIUM CELLULAR MARKET WITH 9800XandM;MINI-PHONEandM;Motorola Inc's new 9800X Personal Cellphone, claimed to be theandM;smallest, lightest cellphone available (CI No 1,165), is part of what thecompany describes as a major effort to dominate the top end of the cellularmarket.andP;  The new product - launched over here at London's Science Museum -measures 6.4&quot; by 2.4&quot; and is either  1.3&quot; or 1.7&quot; thick depending on thebattery: it weighs 12.3oz with the standard battery.andP;  Motorola claims thenext smallest phone on the market is 54% larger than the 9800X.andP;  Thecellphone will be available for all 900MHz analogue systems; it allows up to75 minutes continuous talk time with a standard battery, has 1,320 channels,full ETACS capability and memory for 120 names and numbers.andP;  The next effortsin reducing weight will probably focus on the battery, which weighs 5.6oz instandard form.andP;  At #2,300 - Americans pay only $3,000, the equivalent of#1,765 - the 9800X will be promoted as a premium product, in a industry wherecellphones are increasingly becoming a mass market commodity; UK shipmentsstart this week.andP;  The phone was developed at Motorola's research facilitiesin Arlington Heights, Illinois, and the company has plans to bring productionof the phones to Europe, possibly to its Stotfold facility in the UK; around90% 7of the phone's components are from within Motorola.andP;  The phone has beenlaunched several months before the start of Telepoint service this summer;Motorola, however, maintains that the two products are in separate markets.andO;The new phone will be supplied through Motorola's existing dealers, as wellas the major cellular distributors.andP;  Initial industry reaction appears to befavourable: Millicom Cellular UK Ltd expressed a wish to take the productwithin hours of its launch, and Air Call Cellular Ltd is also set to take the9800X soon.andP;  Both predict strong demand for the phone in the early stages ofits release.andO;</TEXT></DOC>